definitions.definition: ( countable ) A collection , sometimes hidden ; a reserve .
examples: They had quite a stash of food saved up for emergencies.

definitions.definition: ( countable , US , slang , informal , African-American Vernacular ) A place where drugs are stored.
examples: The dealers managed to store the dope in the stash just in time to avoid being caught by the police.

definitions.definition: ( uncountable , UK , slang ) Clothing or other items branded with a particular university club or society 's logo.
examples: We've now ordered stash for everyone who said they wanted some.

definitions.definition: ( countable , textiles ) A collection of yarn or other materials not yet allocated to any particular craft project.
